<item>
            <title>[WICKET-5944] CSRF prevention does not work with https URLs on the default port</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-5944</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If your URL is https on the default port (so no :443 on the end), then the CSRF prevention (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-5919&quot; title=&quot;Add support for CSRF prevention&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-5919&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-5919&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) rejects requests with the Origin header supplied.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In CsrfPreventionRequestCycleListener, line 519 looks like this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (port != -1 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; &quot;http&quot;.equals(scheme) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; port != 80 || &quot;https&quot;.equals(scheme) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; port != 443)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the port != -1 test binds only to the &quot;http&quot; half of the or statement, and the if block executes, which appends &quot;:-1&quot; to the end of the &quot;https&quot; URL. I think it should instead say&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (port != -1 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; (&quot;http&quot;.equals(scheme) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; port != 80 || &quot;https&quot;.equals(scheme) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; port != 443))&lt;/p&gt;</description>
